Persian Gulf Stocks: Aldar Properties and Qatar National Bank

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-09-04T12:39:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-04/persian-gulf-stocks-aldar-properties-and-qatar-national-bank.html
Abu Dhabi’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  fell
for the first time since Aug. 21, slipping 0.1 percent at the 2
p.m. close in the emirate. Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  decreased
0.6 percent, while Qatar’s  QE Index (DSM)  rallied 1.1 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Aldar Properties PJSC (ALDAR)   rose to the highest in a
month, advancing 0.8 percent to 1.25 dirhams. Abu Dhabi’s
biggest real-estate company said its Al-Falah villa project will
be completed in the next year.  Qatar National Bank SAQ (QNBK)   jumped the most since May
11, rising 2.3 percent to 144.9 riyals. The Persian Gulf
country’s biggest lender by assets hired Barclays Plc,  HSBC
Holdings Plc (HSBA)  and QNB Capital to arrange the sale of notes as it
aims to return to the capital market after last November’s
issue.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  